    <fr:title text="Image/Video Diffusion Models">Image/Video Diffusion Models</fr:title>
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter><html:p>This is a crash course in image/video diffusion models as part of CSE 598</html:p>
  <fr:tree show-metadata="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link href="/kellenkanarios/" title="Kellen Kanarios" uri="https://kellenkanarios.com/kellenkanarios/" display-uri="kellenkanarios" type="local">Kellen Kanarios</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:date><fr:year>2025</fr:year><fr:month>9</fr:month><fr:day>8</fr:day></fr:date><fr:title text="Images">Images</fr:title></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
<html:p>Classic denoising is <html:strong>TOO</html:strong> slow for images</html:p>
<html:p>Idea: compress images into latent representation space. Then learn diffusion model on latent space. This is the idea in <html:em>Stable Diffusion</html:em></html:p>
<html:ol><html:li>How do we scale? Use Transformers! Diffusion Transformer (DiT)</html:li>
  <html:li>Still too slow. Enter flow matching.</html:li></html:ol>
<html:p>(1) + (2) = Stable Diffusion 3.</html:p>

    <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link href="/kellenkanarios/" title="Kellen Kanarios" uri="https://kellenkanarios.com/kellenkanarios/" display-uri="kellenkanarios" type="local">Kellen Kanarios</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:date><fr:year>2025</fr:year><fr:month>9</fr:month><fr:day>8</fr:day></fr:date><fr:taxon>Remark</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
